ople  overviewboard memberscommittees executive profile thomas f mclarty iiipresident and cofounder mclarty associatesagetotal calculated compensationthis person is connected to  board members in  different organizations across  different industriessee board relationships background mr thomas f mclarty iii also known as mack serves as the president at mclarty associates he serves as an executive vice chairman at rljmclartylanders automotive holdings llc since october   mr mclarty serves as an advisor at verdeo group inc mr mclarty serves as senior advisor of the carlyle group lp and at covington  burling he is a cofounder and chairman of mclarty associates and serves as its presidentmr mclarty began his business career building  mclarty leasing systems mclarty companies mr mclarty serves as the non executive chairman and prior to april  mr mclarty was the chief executive officer of the mclarty companies he serves as the chairman at mclarty capital partners llc in addition mr mclarty is senior counselor to the center for strategic and international studies he serves as a senior international fellow at the us chamber of commerce mr mclarty was a senior advisor at monument capital group llc he served as chairman chief executive officer member of the board of directors of centerpoint energy arkla in  he became the youngest member ever elected to the board of directors of the arkla gasarkla inc mr mclarty served as special limited partner at forstmann little  co he was cofounder of kissinger mclarty capital group in  he became arklas chairman and chief executive officer and served in that position until joining the white house in  mr mclarty spent a decade as chairman and chief executive officer of the firm mr mclarty was cofounder of rubikon partners he also worked with president carter was appointed to the national petroleum council and the national council on environmental quality by president george hw bush and served on the st louis federal reserve board from  until joining the clinton administration in  mr mclarty was affiliated with the clinton white house from  through  during which time he acted in several capacities he was appointed to two commissions by president bush and served under president clinton in several key positions including the white house chief of staff from  to  counselor to the president and special envoy to the americas in which capacity he was a key mover and shaker in the creation of nafta and the free trade area of the americas ftaa with over five years of service in the presidents cabinet and on the national economic council as white house chief of staff mr mclarty helped enact the historic  deficit reduction package the north american free trade agreement the family and medical leave law and the landmark welfare reform legislation that enabled more than  million people to move from welfare to work he served as a key liaison to clinton for rockefellers council in the implementation of this trade agreement and also organized the successful  summit of the americas in miami which ultimately led to his appointment as special envoy for the americas in  as counselor to the president he advised on a broad range of international and domestic issues mr mclarty traveled to the persian gulf on the presidents behalf to build financial support for the bosnian peace process led the us delegation to the inauguration of south korean president kim daejung signed the peace accords that brought peace to guatemala for the first time in three decades he planned us participation in the  summit of the americas in santiago and participated in several g and apec summits mr mclarty began his political career in  when he was elected to the state legislature of arkansas and served as chairman of the state democratic party from  to  and later served as treasurer for both david pryors and bill clintons gubernatorial campaigns he was appointed by president bush to the national petroleum council and the national council on environmental quality upon leaving the white house in july  mr mclarty became president of an international advisory firm in  he launched rljmclartylanders he served as chairman of rljmclartylanders automotive holdings llc and its vice chairman until october   mr mclarty served as vice chairman of asbury automotive group inc from may  to july   he serves on the boards of the bush clinton katrina fund the council of the americas the interamerican dialogue religions for peace fords theatre and the center for the study of the presidency mr mclarty has been a director of union pacific corporation since november   he is an advisor at leeds equity patners llc he is an advisor of blackstreet capital management llc and leeds equity partners llc he serves as an advisory board member of monument capital group llc coda automotive inc db climate change advisors mr mclarty served as director of commercial national bank tiffin ohio and entergy corporation he was a member of advisory board at diligence london and emerging markets private equity association he served as director of greenstreet acquisition corp mr mclarty served as chairman of nortesur partners he served as nonexecutive chairman and non executive director of asbury automotive arkansas llc from april   to july   he served as director of acxiom corporation from  to august   and convoy solutions llc and idleaire inc since may  mr mclarty served as director of ross university management inc mr mclarty is the recipient of the secretary of states distinguished service medal presented by madeleine albright the order of the aztec eagle presented at los pinos by mexican president ernesto zedillo the fair share award from the naacp the highest civilian honors of argentina brazil chile mexico nicaragua panama and venezuela and the center for the study of the presidency distinguished service award he has been honored with the national conference for community and justice award and the american natural gas association humanitarian award public service award he is a frequent public speaker and has published numerous articles on us trade and foreign policy he has a distinguished record of business leadership and public service including various roles advising three us president bill clinton george h w bush and jimmy carter mr mclarty was awarded an honorary doctorate from his alma mater in  he graduated summa cum laude with a degree in business administration from the university of arkansas in read full background corporate headquarters  th street nwwashington district of columbia united statesphone fax  board members memberships former directorross university management incexecutive vice chairmanrljmclartylanders automotive holdings llcchairman of the boardmclarty capital partners llcpresentindependent directorunion pacific corporation education unknownother education university of arkansas  fayettevillehonorary doctorate university of arkansas  fayetteville other affiliations forstmann little  cothe carlyle group lpleeds equity partners llcacxiom corporationasbury automotive group inccommercial national bank tiffin ohioentergy corporationunion pacific corporationross university management inccenterpoint energy arklakissinger mclarty capital groupblackstreet capital management llcuniversity of arkansas  fayettevillenortesur partnersdiligence londonemerging markets private equity associationrubikon partnersidleaire incgreenstreet acquisition corpmonument capital group llcrljmclartylanders automotive holdings llccoda automotive incverdeo group incdb climate change advisorsmclarty capital partners llc annual compensation there is no annual compensation data available stocks options there is no stock options data available total compensation there is no total compensation data available request profile update   the information and data displayed in this profile are created and managed by sp global market intelligence a division of sp global bloombergcom does not create or control the content for inquir