strategic advisory firm mclarty associates global strategies mclarty inbound africa india  south asia australia  new zealand japan  korea middle east  north africa china southeast asia europe  eurasia brazil  southern cone star central america star mexico star canada andean region star star star star star star star star star star star star star star star star our people star star financial markets star global strategies star film  entertainment star food  agriculture industry experience consumer products food  agriculture energy health film  entertainment high tech financial markets financial services mclarty inboundclose mclarty inbound provides foreign firms seeking to do business in the united states with help on government relations—at the federal state and local levels—strategic planning market access mergers and acquisitions corporate communications and political and economic risk issues mclarty inbounds clients benefit from our substantive regional expertise in trade investment energy food and agriculture hightech and telecommunications and consumer products among many other sectors click here to visit our mclarty inbound page africaclose our africa team includes former senior us government officials with decades of regional experience as well as businesspeople who have worked in key sectors including energy commodities and telecommunications we help our clients seize this dynamic region’s opportunities and navigate its complex commercial barriers click here to visit our africa page india  south asiaclose the members of our washingtonbased team have lived in every major country in south asia have decades of experience traveling to the region speak the principal languages fluently and have served at some of the highest levels of the us government focused on this dynamic region in addition we enjoy a close ontheground partnership with dua consulting in new delhi supplementing our expert capabilities with seasoned indian government affairs professionals and an extensive network of former indian government officials click here to visit our india  south asia page australia  new zealandclose mclarty associates’ regional agricultural and energy expertise is especially wellsuited to the australia and new zealand economies as is our ability to provide uptodate information and strategic advice related to trade and the geopolitics of asia and the indopacific we bring deep ties and wellestablished relationships at senior levels of government business and finance to help us australian and new zealand companies enter expand partner and invest throughout the region and beyond click here to visit our australia  new zealand page japan  koreaclose our japan and korea team includes diplomats and business leaders who have operated at the top levels of those countries for decades and are fluent in the region’s languages business environments and political cultures we have advised american companies working in japan and korea as well as japanese and korean companies invested globally and have decades of experience interacting with regional business leaders as well as close ties with the american chamber of commerce in japan and the korea society in new york click here to visit our japan  korea page middle east  north africaclose mclarty associates’ seasoned middle east and arabian gulf team is comprised of senior officials from both the united states and the middle east with decades of experience conducting regional business and diplomacy we use our trusted role as bridgebuilders to assist western companies entering the region as well as middle eastern companies expanding into international markets click here to visit our middle east  north africa page chinaclose mclarty associates’ china practice is headed by internationally respected diplomats who have been travelling to the region for  years have worked at the highest levels of the chinese government and are regularly consulted by the chinese leadership together with our partners at the scowcroft group we offer our clients uptodate ontheground insights and analysis including sophisticated government relations capabilities at the national provincial and local levels click here to visit our china page southeast asiaclose our southeast asia practice includes some of the most experienced american and foreign diplomats alive today a number of whom were raised or have lived in the region for decades our washingtonbased team is ably supported not only by associates in jakarta hanoi bangkok and manila but also by our partnership with hanoibased indochina bay global whose ontheground reach extends to vietnam cambodia and laos click here to visit our southeast asia page europe  eurasiaclose our europe team includes leading former officials from the united states europe and the former soviet union with knowledge access and networks that reach from manchester to madrid to moscow through a strategic partnership with trident group we offer political and economic risk assessment risk management and government advisory services for clients considering or engaged in business in russia and the former soviet union click here to visit our europe  eurasia page invsting in the usclose popup text brazil  southern coneclose no region has commanded more of mclarty associates’ focus than brazil and the southern cone our team includes former diplomats and trade negotiators treasury officials and native brazilians with experience negotiating that country’s complex business and political environment our senior network of local associates includes some of brazil’s most respected statesmen who serve as a valuable resource for our client work click here to visit our brazil  southern cone page central americaclose our teams distinguished members have lived in a number of central american countries served in high level policymaking positions and been at the forefront of regional policies and developments for decades we bring this deep personal experience and familiarity to bear on our clients’ behalf helping clients forge productive relationships across the region’s diverse political and business landscape click here to visit our central america page mexicoclose our firm’s leadership and team have been actively involved in shaping events and business opportunities in mexico for over a decade and are committed to making sure our clients take advantage of mexico’s tremendous potential our team includes former ambassadors – both american and mexican – senior officials trade negotiators and business leaders with decades of experience in both governments working at the highest levels of usmexico relations click here to visit our mexico page canadaclose our canada team includes former ambassadors and senior officials from both the us and canadian governments we have decades of experience managing many aspects of the uscanada trade and investment relationship as well as deep knowledge of ottawa and the canadian provinces click here to visit our canada page andean regionclose our andean region team includes former ambassadors seasoned diplomats and senior government officials who have been deeply involved in the development of regional policies for decades we’ve helped our clients succeed in this complex region through periods of dramatic political change and our longstanding political and business ties have enhanced our capabilities in industries as diverse as infrastructure energy consumer goods transportation technology media and financial services click here to visit our andean region page financial marketsclose mclarty associates’ financial markets practice harnesses the reach and depth of the firm’s global insights and analysis translating them into effective strategies for a broad range of financial institutions our practice is led by two professionals with extensive experience advising leading financial players including hedge funds banks and asset managers our service is customized to the needs of specific institutions both in terms of scope and delivery whether they are long term investors risk managers or corporate leaders click here to visit our financial markets page global strategiesclose mclarty associates’ global strategies group comprises our firm’s senior leadership with broad global reach to provide our corporate and nonprofit clients with guidance on trans and international issues they may face from advising on the world’s largest corporate merger and the largest private equity leveraged buyout to advising ceos and boards on major strategic decisions and helping clients develop their international government relations capabilities our global strategies team helps our clients navigate between washington and the international arena click here to visit our global strategies  firm leadership page film  entertainmentclose mclarty media our film and entertainment practice advises major film studios directors producers and screenwriters on issues of international interest covering story development authentic script content unique location requirements and complex production logistics our team includes former diplomats government officials and intelligence experts with decades of international experience who are practiced in working with filmmakers click here to visit our film  entertainment page food  agricultureclose the food and agriculture sector continues to grow in importance and complexity as the need to feed the world’s growing population continues to increase while the increased demand for food presents opportunities many challenges exist in the industry in the forms of local protectionism health regulations government interference and marketentry barriers mclarty associates’ knowledge of the food and agriculture industry our familiarity with international trade rules and our foreign market experience allow us to help companies and investors overcome these challenges and achieve success overseas click here to visit our food  agriculture page news  announcements see all announcements » mack mclarty talks about the complicated dynamic between the white house and congress on npr mack mclarty shared his experiences of working with congress while chief of staff at the white house and getting through legislation he was joined by tom davis former virginia congressman npr july   read more » mclarty associates and ejm associates announce strategic partnership moniz and mclarty launch energy consultancy for immediate release july   washington july  – thomas f ‘’mack’’ mclarty iii chairman and cofounder of mclarty associates and former secretary of energy ernest j moniz are proud to announce the launch of their strategic partnership in ejm associates a premier energy consultancy ejm associates  read more » mack mclarty discusses the july legislative agenda healthcare reform and more mack mclarty appeared on the cnbc power lunch television broadcast to discuss the agenda for congress this month healthcare reform and tax reform  and all the challenges that lay ahead cnbc power lunch july   read more »  seventeenth street nw suite  washington dc   p    infomaglobalcom   mack mclarty –  encyclopedia of arkansas home about the encyclopedia  get involved  resources  helpful tips  site map  contact us browse entries alphabetically category type time period race  ethnicity gender browse multimedia galleries category time period type race  ethnicity gender        advanced search print this page           home  browse  mclarty mack mack mclarty – aka thomas franklin mclarty iii thomas franklin “mack” mclarty iii was the first arkansan to serve as white house chief of staff a kindergarten classmate and lifelong friend of president bill clinton mclarty served as clinton’s chief of staff from  to  and later as his special envoy for the americas he is now president of mclarty associates originally kissinger mclarty associates an international advisory firm created in partnership with former secretary of state henry kissinger mack mclarty was born on june   in hope hempstead county to thomas f mclarty jr and helen hesterly mclarty he has one younger brother his father owned and operated an automobile dealership started by mclarty’s grandfather his mother active in community and charitable endeavors became the first woman named to the arkansas industrial development commission the forerunner of the arkansas economic development commission aedc mclarty was raised in hope and graduated from hope high school he and clinton attended kindergarten at miss mary purkins school he was an allstate high school quarterback and was elected governor of arkansas boys state he graduated summa cum laude from the university of arkansas ua in fayetteville washington county in  receiving a ba in business administration he was ua student body president and initiated the school’s first mass transit system after graduation he returned to hope where he helped expand mclarty companies the family auto business of which he still serves as chairman at twentythree he was elected state representative but served only one term choosing not to seek reelection because of growing business responsibilities from  to  he was chief executive officer of arkla inc a fortune  natural gas company with headquarters in shreveport louisiana and little rock pulaski county in  he married donna cochran of texarkana miller county whom he met while attending ua they have two sons clinton chose mclarty as white house chief of staff because of their long friendship his trust in mclarty’s judgment and skill and mclarty’s successful experiences in both the public and private sector which included positions to which he was appointed by clinton’s predecessor as president george h w bush during his tenure as chief of staff mclarty championed the  deficit reduction package that led the federal budget from a deficit to a surplus for the first time since  he played key roles in the passage of the north american free trade agreement nafta the family and medical leave act and welfare reform legislation his collegial demeanor and bipartisan outreach as chief of staff earned him the nickname “mack the nice” which some portrayed as a lack of toughness in imposing discipline in the clinton white house but others contended that mclarty’s niceness and inclusive approach were key to the passage of nafta and welfare reform while helping bridge partisan and philosophical divides mclarty resigned his post as chief of staff to become white house counselor for the americas which led to his being named special envoy to the americas in that post mclarty served as the white house coordinator for the  olympic games in atlanta georgia and received the olympic shield the highest award given by the us olympic committee in  he received the secretary of state’s distinguished service medal for his work in international relations after leaving government service he cofounded kissinger mclarty associates a firm that offers strategic advisory and advocacy services to us and multinational companies in addition he is a senior adviser for the carlyle private equity group and is director of both union pacific and acxiom he has served on the boards of the bushclinton katrina fund the council of the americas the interamerican dialogue fords theatre and the center for the study of the presidency he is a senior international fellow at the us chamber of commerce and is a member of the council on foreign relationsmclarty maintains offices in new york city washington dc and little rock he has residences in washington dc little rock and hope for additional information“big mack” the new republic july   p  friedman samantha “thomas franklin mclarty iii” arkansas democratgazette april   pp d d“thomas f mclarty” in almanac of famous people th ed detroit gale   “thomas f mclarty iii” in marquis who’s who chicago marquis who’s who  “washington notebook clinton visit caps mclartys goodbye party” arkansas democratgazette july   p  james l “skip” rutherford iiiclinton school of public service last updated  